parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can lead to a lack of warning in emergency situations, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The horn stops working
no sound is produced when the horn is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling and engine failure can cause the vehicle to lose power and coast to the side of the road, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or breaks down
often on the highway
with multiple warning lights illuminated on the dashboard (check engine
battery
oil
etc.)
and the onboard Bluelink system may not register an error code.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS sensor can cause a range of warning lights to appear on the dashboard, including forward collision warning, rear cross traffic warning, cruise control warning, and vehicle stability control warning, which can lead to a loss of vehicle control, making it difficult to steer, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Multiple warning lights appear on the dashboard
including ABS
forward collision warning
rear cross traffic warning
cruise control warning
and vehicle stability control warning; steering becomes heavy and difficult to control; loss of vehicle stability; increased risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repairs and Parts Distribution Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repairs and parts distribution can put vehicle owners at risk, as they are left driving vehicles with known safety defects, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle owners receive recall notifications but are unable to schedule repairs due to unavailable parts
dealerships confirm parts availability only to cancel appointments
and manufacturers prioritize new
unsold cars over cars already in use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair recalled seat belts can lead to accidents or injuries, as the faulty seat belts may not provide adequate protection in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Vehicle owners receive recall notifications for seat belt defects
but parts are not available for repair
dealerships cancel appointments due to lack of parts
and manufacturers fail to provide timely repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: 8-Speed Dual Clutch Transmission (DCT) Shudder and Sluggish Engagement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shudder and sluggish engagement of the 8-speed DCT can cause hesitation or delay when accelerating from a stop, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when merging into traffic or crossing intersections.
symptoms: The transmission shudders or vibrates when starting from a stop
the transmission is slow to engage or hesitates when shifting into gear
the vehicle is slow to accelerate from a stop
the transmission makes unusual noises or clunking sounds when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission software calibration issues can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to hesitation, delay, or failure to engage gears, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when merging into traffic or crossing intersections.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or delays when shifting into gear
the transmission fails to engage gears
the transmission makes unusual noises or clunking sounds when shifting
the vehicle is slow to accelerate from a stop.
